d 'XTPQROOT': module to provide Panel Quantile Unit Root Tests with Common Shocks & Structural Breaks
d
d   xtpqroot implements two novel panel unit root tests designed
d for panel data with cross-sectional	 dependence (CSD):	 
d 1) CIPS(tau) Test: Quantile panel unit root test with common
d shocks, proposed by Yang, Wei &	     Cai (2022, Economics
d Letters). It extends Pesaran's (2007) CIPS test to a quantile    
d	 regression framework, allowing the analysis of asymmetric
d persistence across different		  quantiles of the
d conditional distribution. While the standard CIPS test assesses
d the mean	      persistence, CIPS(tau) can detect, for
d example, whether a series is more persistent in	    
d extreme quantiles than in the center. Implementation follows
d Nazlioglu, Tarakci, Karul &		 Erdem (2026, NAJEF).	   
d  2) tFR Test: Panel unit root test with smooth and sharp
d structural breaks, proposed by	    Corakci & Omay (2023,
d Renewable Energy). It combines the fractional Fourier function
d (for		  smooth, gradual breaks) with the logistic smooth
d transition (LST) function (for sharp, 	   abrupt breaks).
d This allows the test to capture {bf:both types of structural
d change	    simultaneously}. Cross-sectional dependence is
d corrected via the sieve bootstrap	       procedure of Chang
d (2004). 
d
d KW: time series
d KW: panel data
d KW: quantile
d KW: unit root
d KW: Common Shocks
d KW: Structural Breaks
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260228
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f xtpqroot.ado
f xtpqroot.sthlp
f ../_/_xtpqroot_cips.ado
f ../_/_xtpqroot_fourier.ado
